Summary: <start>Trey Moses, a college basketball star, asked Ellie Meredith, a high school freshman with Down syndrome, to be his prom date. Trey, who is going to play basketball at Ball State next year, originally planned to take his girlfriend to the prom but changed his mind after meeting Ellie. He made the prom-posal in the gym during Ellie's P.E. class and she tearfully accepted. The teacher at Eastern High School, Trina Helson, posted the photos of Trey and Ellie on Twitter which went viral. According to Trey, Ellie is "great" and "easy to talk to." <end> '}
